egration, because the failure is in module handoff/visibility control (Slot B), and Unit misses real wiring leaks to the client path (Slot C). Rejection-gate: Agentic considered, but behavior text explicitly conditions on \"when the tone check triggers\" and validates replacement/visibility, not tone-judgment quality; Workflow disqualified because it does not require validating multiple model decisions' quality." ,"test_description":"Run the integrated request pipeline with tone-check outcome forced to trigger regeneration, then assert client-visible output/stream contains only the regenerated response while the rejected draft is suppressed from user-facing channels.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test needs end-to-end controller + response channel wiring; a lower-level unit cannot verify no leak of first draft.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.63,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.05}}]}
